#                 _quincy-client (multi-bin: quincy-client + quincy-server)
#                                                 [Rust=247 OPENS Axis 192]
#                                                  ↑↑↑ THIS FILE ↑↑↑
#
#     Go      : (next round — Go=247, slot 2/0/0)
#                Canonical Go QUIC: github.com/quic-go/quic-go by
#                Marten Seemann (formerly libp2p / Protocol Labs) —
#                pure-Go IETF QUIC v1 implementation with HTTP/3
#                support via the sibling quic-go/http3 package.  Used
#                by Caddy 2's HTTP/3 server, cilium/cilium's
#                Hubble UI, syncthing, qudo, gost (a tunnel proxy),
#                and the broader Go HTTP/3 ecosystem.  [TBD next-
#                round consumer]
#
#     JS/Node : (Axis 192 CLOSES at TS-Node=247, slot 1/1/1)
#                Canonical JS QUIC: this lane is the tricky one
#                because Node.js's QUIC story has been in flux.  Node
#                15 shipped experimental QUIC behind --experimental-
#                quic but the API was removed in Node 17.  Node 19+
#                ships node-quic 2.x which is OpenSSL-backed but
#                still flagged.  The mature non-Node-builtin option
#                is `@nodejs/node-quic` (which wraps OpenSSL's QUIC
#                support) or `nghttp3-js` (WASM port of nghttp3/
